OL,3,CWorld's oldest topiary garden
OL,4,Cundergoes extensive six-month trim
OL,6,FGranada Reports journalist Paul Crone
OL,7,Fwent to see the gardeners starting the
OL,8,Fmammoth task of trimming more than one
OL,9,Fhundred living sculptures
OL,11,FGardeners have started an ambitious
OL,12,Fsix-month trimming of over 100 living
OL,13,Fsculptures in the world's oldest
OL,14,Ftopiary garden.
OL,16,FEstablished in 1694, each year the
OL,17,Fgardens at Levens Hall in Cumbria
OL,18,Fattracts around 30,000 visitors.
