OL,3,CWorld's oldest topiary garden
OL,4,Cundergoes extensive six-month trim
OL,6,FIn addition to topiary care, the
OL,7,Fgardeners are also nurturing 15,000
OL,8,Fflowers and plants in their
OL,9,Fgreenhouse, preparing for the vibrant
OL,10,Fdisplays of spring and summer.
OL,12,FOverseeing this horticultural project
OL,13,Fis Chris Crowder, 61, who has served
OL,14,Fas head gardener at Levens Hall for 38
OL,15,Fyears.
OL,17,FCrowder describes the start of the
OL,18,Fannual trimming as "like New Year's
OL,19,FDay," and he is proud to be the
OL,20,Flongest-serving head gardener at the
OL,21,Festate since the 19th century.
