OL,3,CWorld's oldest topiary garden
OL,4,Cundergoes extensive six-month trim
OL,6,FMany of the trees in the garden have
OL,7,Fbeen there for more than a hundred
OL,8,Fyears some exceeding 330 years.
OL,10,FThe distinctive shapes of the older
OL,11,Ftrees reflect the vision of gardeners
OL,12,Ffrom centuries past. Crowder remains
OL,13,Fcommitted to preserving these original
OL,14,Fdesigns while acknowledging that each
OL,15,Ftree possesses its own unique
OL,16,F"character" that evolves over time.
