OL,3,CWorld's oldest topiary garden
OL,4,Cundergoes extensive six-month trim
OL,6,FLevens Hall is owned by Richard Bagot,
OL,7,F42, whose family has been connected to
OL,8,Fthe estate for five centuries. Bagot
OL,9,Flives on the property with his
OL,10,Ffiancee, Chloe, and their newborn. The
OL,11,Ffamily enjoys the gardens on Saturdays
OL,12,Fwhen the house is closed to the public.
OL,14,FDuring the Covid lockdown in 2020,
OL,15,FBagot initiated World Topiary Day,
OL,16,Fcelebrated on 12 May. This event aims
OL,17,Fto honour both professional and
OL,18,Famateur topiary artists and encourages
OL,19,Findividuals to create their own
OL,20,Ftopiary masterpieces.
